{"id": 225020982, "title": "Five Types Of Personal And Professional Fulfillment And How To Gain Them", "text": "Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Share to Linkedin Bronwen Sciortino, author & simplicity expert teaching easy ways to tailor-make healthy, happy & highly successful lives. sheIQ Life Pty Ltd getty I\u2019ve heard so many stories recently about women who have \"given up\" or \"given in\" and left their jobs because their home life has demanded all of their attention. And when I hear these stories, they\u2019re told by other women with a sigh of frustration lurking beneath the surface ... that yet another woman has \"had to walk away\" from their career because they just can\u2019t manage it all. It\u2019s no secret that women carry a heavy load; the statistics have been there for ages, and it\u2019s something that\u2019s been openly discussed. But here we are, still seeing the effects of it happening on a daily basis. My life collapsed out from under me because I was trying so hard to be it all, have it all and prove it all to the world. I pushed so hard and for so long that I shattered into a million pieces on the floor, and I had to spend three long, hard and rigorous years piecing myself back together. MORE FOR YOU Trump Trial Prosecutor Ends Closing Argument After Nearly 5 Hours\u2014Jury Instructions Set For Wednesday Gas Explosion In Downtown Youngstown Ohio Injures At Least 7 Trump Lashes Out At Robert De Niro After Actor Calls Him A \u2018Tyrant\u2019 Outside Courthouse Is the slog worth it? Where I am now is absolutely worth the journey I went through to get there. But here\u2019s the rub: The slog wasn\u2019t necessary for me to get here. In fact, if there is anything that my personal experience has taught me, it\u2019s that wherever there is \"slog\" there is a clear sign that you\u2019re on the wrong path and that you need to be doing something else\u2014or at least the same thing in a different way. Somewhere along the way, we\u2019ve adopted the slog as a \"rite of passage\" that we have to overcome before we\u2019re allowed to do things differently. In reality, the quicker we give up our obsession with slogging through life, the easier and simpler everything becomes. It\u2019s less about success and all about fulfillment. It\u2019s time to move away from the demands of others\u2014and the definitions given to us by those others around success. By focusing on putting together the unique combination of things that provide fulfillment to create the perfect life that\u2019s right for each individual, it is easier to put down the things that make our life load heavy. We rarely feel the weight of the things that make us laugh, bring us joy and open our hearts in love ... so why wouldn\u2019t we want to fill our lives with these things and crowd out the things that don\u2019t contribute in this way? Every woman deserves to feel like she can make the choices that are right for her life\u2014right now\u2014and that she can mix and match activities in a way that provides her with the flexibility to grow and develop, change and move over time. Let fulfillment enable you. Here are five types of fulfillment that can help enable women to create the life they deserve every day: 1. Personal Growth Whether this is through setting and achieving personal goals, expanding knowledge and skills or embracing new experiences that challenge and enrich life, personal growth is something that every woman deserves: the opportunity to continuously evolve and grow as an individual. 2. Relationships Nurturing meaningful connections with loved ones, friends and/or community members is essential for women\u2019s well-being. This fulfillment stems from fostering healthy, supportive relationships that are built on trust, communication and mutual respect. 3. Career Women deserve to pursue careers that align with their passions, values and aspirations. Career fulfillment is achieved when women find purpose and satisfaction in their work, feel valued for their contributions and have opportunities for growth and advancement. 4. Health And Wellness Prioritizing physical and mental well-being is crucial for overall fulfillment. Women deserve to prioritize self-care, maintain a healthy lifestyle and prioritize activities that promote their physical, mental and emotional health. 5. Legacy Leaving a positive legacy is a meaningful pursuit for every woman. Legacy fulfillment involves making a lasting impact on future generations, whether that be through role-modeling, mentorship, philanthropy or living a life aligned with one\u2019s values and principles. At different times there will be different demands in life that compete for time and resources to be allocated to them. By piecing together different combinations of these five types of fulfillment in line with life\u2019s demands, women can have exactly what they need for themselves while still running around and looking after those around them. In short, every woman deserves to live a life that fills her with joy, purpose and fulfillment. There\u2019s never been a better time to prioritize happiness and well-being. Now\u2019s the time to dive deeper into what it means to live authentically and fully. You can have it all when you choose to take control of your destiny, create the life that\u2019s perfect for you and take simple, practical steps that leave you feeling empowered and living your best life. Forbes Coaches Council is an invitation-only community for leading business and career coaches. Do I qualify? Follow me on LinkedIn. Check out my website. Bronwen Sciortino Editorial Standards Print Reprints & Permissions", "summary": "Take control of your destiny, create the life that\u2019s perfect for you and take simple, practical steps that leave you feeling empowered and living your best life.", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbescoachescouncil/2024/05/29/five-types-of-personal-and-professional-fulfillment-and-how-to-gain-them/", "image": "